register.description: The Module and Version Register identifies the module identifier and revision of the SERDES module.

bitfield.description: The POR_EN allows the system to place the SERDES in a reset state. Accesses to the SERDES registers are ignored.

register.description: The Lane and PLL Status register is used to indicate the current configuration of the REFCLK distribution and Lane Mux selection.

bitfield.description: Indicates the state of the PLL0 REFCLK supplies. 0 - REFCLK power is off 1 - REFCLK power is on

Indicates the chaining for the right side will be opposite of the PLL0_CHAIN_EN field used for the left chaining. 0 - Chaining for left and right will match PLL0_CHAIN_EN field. 1 - Chain left is PLL0_CHAIN_EN field and chain right is !PLL0_CHAIN_EN field.

Indicates the REFCLK source used for PLL0. This bit indicates that the left REFCLK input is used for the PLL0. When both PLL0_LEFT_SEL and PLL0_RIGHT_SEL are zero, the REFCLK pads are used for the PLL0.
Indicates the REFCLK chaining is enabled. 0 - REFCLK right and left are driven from the REFCLK pads of this Serdes 1 - REFCLK right or left is driven from left or right respectively.

Indicates the REFCLK source used for PLL0. This bit indicates that the right REFCLK input is used for the PLL0. When both PLL0_LEFT_SEL and PLL0_RIGHT_SEL are zero, the REFCLK pads are used for the PLL0.
Indicates that the lane 0 tx clock is valid.
Indicates that the selected IF has the Lane 0 reset isolation signal set.
Indicates which interface is used for lane 0. See , Interface Selection

register.description: The SERDES Feature register contains the features of the SERDES.

register.description: The lane x control and status provides the ability to override SERDES configuration settings. It is mainly provided for test, but sometimes used for mission setup as well.

bitfield.description: The Tx Enable Overlay bit, when set allows the Tx Enable Value to override the CFGTX.Enable input.
The Tx Enable Value when used allows the Tx lane to be placed in a 0 - Disable state. 1 - Sleep state. 2 - Snooze state. 3 - Enabled state.
The Tx Rate Overlay bit, when set allows the Tx Rate Value to override the CFGTX.Rate input.
The Tx Rate Value when used allows the Tx lane to be placed into 0 - Full Rate mode. 1 - Half Rate mode. 2 - Quarter Rate mode.
The Tx Idle Overlay bit, when set allows the Tx Idle Value to override the CFGTX.Idle input.
The Tx Idle Value, when used allows the Tx lane to be placed electrical Idle state in non Pipe Interface mode.
The Tx Width Overlay bit, when set allows the Tx Width Value to override the CFGTX.Width input.
The Tx Width Value, when used allows the Tx lane to be placed into 0 - 10 bit mode 1 - 16 bit mode 2 - 20 bit mode 3 - 40 bit mode This field is ignored in Pipe Interface Mode
The Rx Enable Overlay bi,t when set allows the Rx Enable Value to override the CFGRX.Enable input.
The Rx Enable Valu,e when used allows the Rx lane to be placed in a 0 - Disable state. 1 - Sleep state. 2 - Snooze state. 3 - Enabled state.
The Rx Rate Overlay bit, when set allows the Rx Rate Value to override the CFGRX.Rate input.
The Rx Rate Value when used allows the Rx lane to be placed into 0 - Full Rate mode. 1 - Half Rate mode. 2 - Quarter Rate mode.
The Rx Polarity Overlay bit, when set allows the Rx Polarity Value to override the CFGRX.Polarity input.
The Rx Polarity Value, when used allows the lane Rx Polarity to be inverted.
The Rx Align Overlay bit, when set allows the Rx Align Value to override the CFGRX.Align input.
The Rx Align Value, when used allows the Rx lane to align to K28.1, K28.5 and K28.7 characters otherwise known as Comma Characters.
The Rx Width Overlay bit, when set allows the Rx Width Value to override the CFGRX.Width input.
The Rx Width Value when used allows the Rx lane to be placed into 0 - 10-bit mode 1 - 16-bit mode 2 - 20-bit mode 3 - 40-bit mode This field is ignored in Pipe Interface Mode
The Rx OK indicate that the lane is in a functional state.
The Rx Signal Loss Indicates that the data has not been detected or the CDR is not locked.

register.description: The PLL Control register provides the ability to override the PLL state and control events for debug purposes.

bitfield.description: The PLL Enable Overlay bit, when set allows the PLL Enable Value to override the CFGPLL.Enable input.
The PLL Enable Value when used allows the PLL to be placed in a 0 - Disable state. 1 - Sleep state. 2 - Snooze state. 3 - Enabled state.
The PLL Ok indicate that the transmit clocks are valid and the PLL circuits are ready for use.
The LN_WAFTER_OK field will cause the lane OK indication to be Blocked until the LN0_CONT_OK is set. This allows code to run after the lane OK but before the hardware can use the lane.
The LN_WAFTER_SD field will cause the Rx signal indication to be Blocked until the LN0_CONT_SD is set. This allows code to run after signal detect but before the hardware can use the data.
The LN0_CONT_OK allows the Blocked lane OK for lane 0 to now pass to the controlling PCS IP. This bit is auto cleared when LN0_OK_STATE is driven inactive.
The LN0_OK_STATE indicate the current state of the lane OK signal for lane 0.
The LN0_CONT_SD allows the Blocked signal detect for lane 0 to now pass to the controlling PCS IP. This bit is auto cleared when LN0_SD_STATE is driven inactive.
The LN0_SD_STATE indicate the current state of the signal detect signal for lane 0.

register.description: The Comma Link Delay register defines the added delay due to comma alignment for the SERDES lanes. This value should be added to the receive time stamp to accurately time stamp the packet arrival. For a 1G link the value is 800pS per bit. This value may change any time the link is established.

bitfield.description: Defines the number of network bits the comma aligner has added to the fixed delay of the PCS/PMA layer for lane 0.

register.description: The CMU Wait is used to create a 150 micro second delay between the completion of the SERDES configuration writes and activating the SERDES CMU logic allowing for supplies to settle.

bitfield.description: Defines the number of clock cycles times 256 between pll_enable and cmu_master_cdn being set and the cmu_iddq going low.

Defines the number of ~i(WAIT_VAL+1)*~i(PHAN_VAL+1) clock cycles between CMU Reset and when the phantom CMU_OK is generated. This allows the Serdes to start using valid clocks. The Phantom CMU_OK is used in Pipe mode. If this field is 0, the Phantom CMU_OK is equal to the actual CMU_OK.
Defines the number of clock cycles between writing to the CMU Reset register and cmu_reset_i activation. The value should be 150 µs or more.
